ads/2018/12/amp-mobile-news-carousel-300x201.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"201\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHowever, there is a reason why not everyone is jumping on Google AMP wagon. For some brands Googles AMP framework restriction goes against some functionalities important for the brand. Also conveniently AMP It is not flexible in allowingother analytics platforms other than Google Analytics. There is also a limited of widgets available, for example it does not support Facebook like box.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&lt;iframe src=\"https://giphy.com/embed/gOHxskuYRcg3m\" width=\"480\" height=\"270\" frameBorder=\"0\" class=\"giphy-embed\" allowFullScreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=\"https://giphy.com/gifs/mrw-san-housing-gOHxskuYRcg3m\"&gt;via GIPHY&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn conclusion Google is trying to standardize mobile optimization. The promise of a better mobile experience is a great one to have, however, those who dont want to follow the framework shouldnt be punished. Google has the power to make sites and brands obey their mandate because if they refuse they can say goodbye to Googles first page which is something those sites who have that privilege to be on, cant afford.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-111\" src=\"http://whapaso-2.tinselship.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/google-jail-logo-300x119.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"119\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAPM its still at an early stage and Google hasnt given out too many clues as to the influence of the AMP on rankings but as a brand you might want to be considering making the move if you havent done so. God knows you dont want to be on Googles bad side.', 'Google AMP', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '108-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-12-02 04:18:26', '2018-12-02 04:18:26', '', 108, 'http://whapaso-2.tinselship.com/108-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(115, 1, '2018-12-02 04:30:19', '2018-12-02 04:30:19', 'We are on a time where data is quickly catching up to brands expectation. Each day the spillover between non-targeted consumers is getting smaller. Therefore, as brands will be able to exclusively and effectively reach their core consumer the focus will be on the content itself and how to serve the best experience to the consumer. Based on this, native advertising will start taking an even major role in the upcoming years.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1>The promise -</h1>\r\n<h2>Placement:</h2>\r\nConsumers are now used to ad placements and banner size and the brain quickly develops a habit to expect them and ignore them. Native place the ad in the content itself that is being consumed. Because the ad is integrated with the content the customer is not able to ignore the ad.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Effectiveness:</h2>\r\nBased on a recent study by the Mobile Marketing Association the ad placement Native has proven to be ten times more effective than traditional banners. It also shows the consumer interaction and time with the ad is 3 times higher and receives 23 percent higher quality score than display ads.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div style=\"width: 100%; height: 0; padding-bottom: 56%; position: relative;\"><iframe class=\"giphy-embed\" style=\"position: absolute;\" src=\"https://giphy.com/embed/F2WFyAfpfVfFe\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>The worries:</h2>\r\nPrice: Native advertising can be significantly more expensive. Even if it does perform better than display, brands has to be sure they are not paying exponentially more than the increase on performance.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Perception:</h2>\r\nNative ads heavily depends on how its being executed, like any piece of content, however because of the flawless placement if the ad is not perfectly executed not only the consumer wont like it but they will feel the brand is being sneaky and cheated.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class=\"tenor-gif-embed\" data-postid=\"5283932\" data-share-method=\"host\" data-width=\"100%\" data-aspect-ratio=\"1.6\"><a href=\"https://tenor.com/view/theoffice-michaelscott-cheated-cheater-canttrust-gif-5283932\">Theoffice Michaelscott GIF</a> from <a href=\"https://tenor.com/search/theoffice-gifs\">Theoffice GIFs</a></div>\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\" async src=\"https://tenor.com/embed.js\"></script>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1>The future -</h1>\r\nNative advertising is the future. For the past years the advertising world has been focusing in making sure they are at the right placement in the right time and now that we are almost there the focus will shift into making sure the content is not being ignored. IHS Markit projects that by 2020, 63.2% of mobile display advertising will be native.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe believe that technology and brands will also find a way to avoid the high cost publishers charge for Native and agencies will build expertise on execution to guarantee that the user experience matches the content expectations.', 'Native is the Future of Advertising', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'native-is-the-future-of-advertising', '', '', '2018-12-03 15:12:17', '2018-12-03 15:12:17', '', 0, 'http://whapaso-2.tinselship.com/?p=115', 3, 'post', '', 0),
