(125, 1, '2018-12-02 05:24:03', '2018-12-02 05:24:03', 'Nope, no, no, please no!! Whoever came out with the outstream video format most be a very annoying person. It reminds me of when as a kid I was forced to eat spinach soup even if I never asked for it and definitely never wanted it. Every time that happened I puked, a similar feeling I have when I see an outstream video ad showing up unannounced in-between content I am engaging with. They call it native video ad, but this is a misleading term, it does not have anything native, is invasive, is intrusive, is a spoon fill of spinach soup pushed down your throat for those who have a similar taste as me.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div style=\"width: 100%; height: 0; padding-bottom: 43%; position: relative;\"><iframe class=\"giphy-embed\" style=\"position: absolute;\" src=\"https://giphy.com/embed/3owzVQ23NzdKvVALUA\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLets ad the following into the mix; survey done by video company Unruly showed that 92 percent of 3,200 internet users surveyed said that they\'d consider using an ad blocker and 62 percent of people said that they are annoyed by preroll ads. This study was done before the increase in outstream video we are seeing now and that we will be experiencing in the future.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThis format is fairly new and at least at this moment the execution is far from great. The ad will definitely be seen but brands and publishers have to think twice before using it as it has a high potential to bring a negative brand perception for the advertiser and some traffic lost for the publisher.', 'We Hate Outstream Video', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'we-hate-outstream-video', '', '', '2018-12-03 09:31:47', '2018-12-03 09:31:47', '', 0, 'http://whapaso-2.tinselship.com/?p=125', 1, 'post', '', 0),
